---
title: Brown Sugar Bourbon Steak with Honey Dijon Salad & Green Beans
description: Pork chops are always a dinner winner. They’re satisfying, speedy, and so versatile, which is why our chefs are always thinking up new ways to take them to the next level. This week, they amped up the flavors... big time. Sweet and savory is the name of the game here. Tender chops are coated in brown sugar bourbon spice (which is all kinds of savory-sweet in and of itself), then seared and topped with a buttery apple pan sauce. Roasted green beans and a honey Dijon salad pair perfectly with the main event. Prepare yourself for a flavor explosion.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62276ef45bbcb479142b810b-7b2ce35e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/brown-sugar-bourbon-steak-62276ef45bbcb479142b810b-246b9a49.pdf
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 30 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1160 mg
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/brown-sugar-bourbon-steak-62276ef45bbcb479142b810b
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Set aside until ready to roast in step 3.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Season all over with @brown sugar bourbon seasoning{10.8%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> If the pork begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer steak to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in steak for pork; cook to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

While steak cooks, transfer baking sheet with green beans to oven. Roast on middle rack until lightly browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and dice @apple{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add apple and scallion whites; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Cook until sauce has thickened and apple is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

In the last ~{2%minutes}, return steak to pan until warmed through. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce} and @walnuts{1/2%ounce} with @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} (start with half and add more if you like).

Divide steak, salad, and green beans between plates. Top steak with apple pan sauce. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.